g.com/originals/3c/e2/c2/3ce2c2e0c3fb9aacfecca4e1d3b3161f.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQeT1rNU8wrXtSl0dyHtRXu_LoAfeSgKL4sp0UgXX6NVtQ7G3BJLFg-UuRwtPGFGX2ju2U";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:300;s:6:"height";i:300;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/758364024741411492/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:42:"garage door closes and opens right back up";s:4:"slug";s:42:"garage-door-closes-and-opens-right-back-up";s:5:"title";s:158:"Upgrade Your Home Security With Integrated Smart Home Features Garage Door Control Lets You Check Wheth Home Security Systems Home Security Home Security Tips";s:3:"alt";s:158:"upgrade your home security with integrated smart home features garage door control lets you check wheth home security systems home security home security tips";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/cb/93/a8/cb93a870c8d433f83d650c159f8afaa1.png";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTxAVMGbSWEWEFdaSCnXKPzKn0MJj_l9PrJ6w";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:1430;s:6:"height";i:600;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/335729347214640195/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:53:{i:0;s:71:"Possible Reasons Why Your Garage Door Hits the Floor Then Goes Back Up.";i:1;s:107:"As is the case with so many issues at the home theres no one reason why your garage door closes then opens.";i:2;s:70:"Heres a rundown of some of the possible reasons this can be happening.";i:3;s:34:"Your Travel Down Setting Needs to.";i:4;s:127:"Shortly after when the homeowner goes to close the Garage Door it will only close about 4-6 inches and goes right back to open.";i:5;s:66:"Simply turning them towards each other can realign the photo eyes.";i:6;s:67:"Make sure that the light on each eye is lit solid and not blinking.";i:7;s:74:"Once you have done this the Garage Door will function properly once again.";i:8;s:39:"They are connected to the opener motor.";i:9;s:94:"An invisible beam passes from one of the devices to the other between the garage door opening.";i:10;s:141:"If there is anything that interrupts or breaks that beam when the garage door is trying to close the door is going to reverse and go back up.";i:11;s:66:"The garage doors also have a second system for automatic reversal.";i:12;s:183:"Incorrect travel settings When your garage door is installed the opener is programmed with a number that indicates how far down the door is expected to travel before its fully closed.";i:13;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:14;s:38:"Here are some symptoms of the problem.";i:15;s:39:"The garage door goes down then back up.";i:16;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:17;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:18;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:19;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:20;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:21;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:22;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:23;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:24;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:25;s:57:"My garage door closes and then immediately opens back up.";i:26;s:29:"Was working fine before this.";i:27;s:71:"How do I correct this - Answered by a verified Home Improvement Expert.";i:28;s:219:"If the door only does this with the remote and you need to hold the wall switch button continuously to bring the door down then there could be a problem with the safety sensors near the bottom of the garage door itself.";i:29;s:94:"Again the opener would see a problem there as a potential safety concern and re-open the door.";i:30;s:42:"Garage Door goes right back up every time.";i:31;s:113:"When I use the remote or wall button to close my garage door as soon as it hits the ground it goes right back up.";i:32;s:103:"To get it to stay down once it hits the ground I push the button on the remote again and it stays down.";i:33;s:75:"Its been doing this for about a year and now that were planning on selling.";i:34;s:76:"Another common cause of garage doors acting this way is a faulty RPM sensor.";i:35;s:91:"Consult your owners manual or a trained garage door technician in replacing the RPM sensor.";i:36;s:74:"Parts can be purchased in online stores or directly from the manufacturer.";i:37;s:60:"If this has been helpful please click the green accept icon.";i:38;s:191:"When a garage door descends on command but then immediately reverses itself the problem is usually with the sensor eyes along the side tracks or with the doors wheels binding in their tracks.";i:39;s:146:"But when the door begins to descend all on its own the problem may point to the openers logic board or the circuitry inside the motor unit itself.";i:40;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:41;s:112:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse whenever it hits an obstruction such as the driveway or ground.";i:42;s:45:"You push the button to close the garage door.";i:43;s:63:"It goes partway down reverses direction and goes back up again.";i:44;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";i:45;s:33:"Garage Door Closes Opens Back Up.";i:46;s:59:"Press the button on your remote to operate the garage door.";i:47;s:77:"If it closes and then begins to open again you need to adjust the down limit.";i:48;s:133:"Using a flathead screwdriver turn the down limit switch adjustment screw on the side of the garage door opener clockwise by one turn.";i:49;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:50;s:49:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse.";i:51;s:159:"If your garage door opener lights blink 8 times it means that you have a Chamberlain Craftsman or LiftMaster opener and will confirm that it is a sensor issue.";i:52;s:154:"The first thing to check would be the lights on the front of the sensors down at the bottom left and right of the door and confirm that they are both lit.";}}